You have been provided some customer data from a shopping centre. Do some exploratory analysis on the data. Comment on findings.

We are interested in creating a marketing campaign to target customers based on their spending score and annual income. Perform a k-means clustering to find if there are meaningful clusters in the data to target the customers.

# customers_subet is the scaled data set
# need to create a data set with the two variables I want 

customers_two_var <- customers %>% 
  select(annual_income_k, spending_score_1_100)

k_clusters <- tibble(k = 1:20) %>% 
  mutate(
    kclust = map(k, ~kmeans(x = customers_subset, centers = .x, nstart = 25)),
    tidied = map(kclust, tidy),
    glanced = map(kclust, glance),
    augmented = map(kclust, ~augment(.x, customers_two_var))
  )

k_clusters

5 clusters seems like a good fit for the data, silhouette method recommended 5

data seems like a good fit for clustering, 5 distinct groups easily binned

labels:

bottom left - low income / low spending score (fiscally responsible) bottom right - high income / low spending score (savers) centre - medium income / medium spending score top left - low income / high spending score (irresponsible spenders) top right - high income / high spenders
